<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,809,1050]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,809,834]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized oscinelline with vertex of head rounded in lateral view, small trapezoidal scutellum with short or undifferentiated sub-apical scutellar bristles, anal angle of wing reduced, elongated and narrowed abdomen, and male cerci fused medially into a single sclerite male cerci fused medially into a single sclerite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,809,1050]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,917,942]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Description.</emphasis>
This genus was described by Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler (2010b) and thus a detailed description is not included here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,809,1050]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,495,989,1014]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
